1. MIMIC-III / MIMIC-IV (Medical Information Mart for Intensive Care)

Description: Contains de-identified health-related data of ICU patients.

Includes: Vitals, labs, medications, diagnoses (ICD codes), demographics, etc.

Use Case: Disease prediction, mortality prediction, readmission risk, etc.

Link: https://physionet.org/content/mimiciv/2.2/

Access: Requires credentialed access (free after completing a data use agreement and course).


2. UCI Machine Learning Repository - Heart Disease Dataset

Description: Patient data for predicting the presence of heart disease.

Includes: Age, sex, chest pain type, resting BP, cholesterol, etc.

Use Case: Binary classification (heart disease present or not).

Link: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Heart+Disease


3. Diabetes 130-US hospitals Dataset

Description: 10 years of clinical care data from diabetic patients.

Includes: 100,000+ records, lab results, medication, readmission.

Use Case: Predicting diabetes complications, hospital readmission.

Link: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/diabetes+130-us+hospitals+for+years+1999-2008


4. Breast Cancer Wisconsin Dataset

Description: Diagnostic data for breast cancer classification.

Includes: Cell nucleus characteristics.

Use Case: Classifying benign vs malignant tumors.

Link: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Breast+Cancer+Wisconsin+(Diagnostic)


5. COVID-19 Data Repository (Johns Hopkins, Kaggle, etc.)

Description: Real-time and historical data on COVID-19.

Use Case: Predicting infection risk, severity, or outcomes.

Link: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/imdevskp/corona-virus-report
